CR Prospect Campaign Specification Instance Record	CR Prospect Campaign Specification Instance Record	Prospect Campaign Specification Instance Record	##			The overall record for a prospect campaign design	IO	IO			IO	IO	IO	O
			Prospect Campaign Type			The type or category of prospect campaign (e.g. direct acquisition, product discount incentive)	IO	IO				IO	IO	O
			Prospect Campaign Description			A description of the campaign that clarifies the intended context/use of the campaign, the mechanisms employed and the intended/anticipated response/impact	IO	IO				IO	IO	O
			Prospect Campaign Metrics	##		Metrics that are defined to assess the target and actual impact of the campaign	IO	IO				IO	IO	O
				Prospect Campaign Metric Definition		A description of the metric, defining how it is to be measured in deployment	IO	IO				IO	IO	O
				Prospect Campaign Metric Goal		A description of the target performance for the metric that can be defined for different usage scenarios as appropriate	IO	IO				IO	IO	O
			Prospect Campaign Specification	##		The precise make-up of the campaign. Note that all prospect campaign specifications are subject to versioning as the campaign is refined over time.	O	IO				O	O	O
				Prospect Campaign Product/Service Usage	##	Details how the campaign aligns with selected products and services, including pricing considerations	O	IO				O	O	O
					Prospect Campaign Product/Service Type	The type or category of product or service included in the campaign (e.g. current account)	O	IO				O	O	O
					Product/Service Campaign Engagement Description	A description of how the product or service is adapted in the context of the campaign (e.g. discounted pricing/preferential rates, waived service fees, gifts or incentives)	O	IO				O	O	O
					Product/Service Campaign Transfer Pricing Arrangement	Describes how any discounted costs are to be accounted for by the product fulfillment function (e.g. borne by fulfillment business unit, compensated by campaign budget)	O	IO				O	O	O
				Prospect Campaign Execution Guidelines	##	Guidelines for the execution of the campaign	O	IO				O	O	O
					Prospect Campaign Eligibility 	Defines the eligibility criteria that are to be applied to select suitable candidates for the prospect campaign. (Note candidate lists are developed by Campaign Execution)	O	IO				O	O	O
					Prospect Campaign Qualifications	Defines any qualifications or credentials required of the bank unit or employees to execute the campaign (e.g. product certified, sign-off authority level)	O	IO				O	O	O
					Prospect Campaign Interaction Guide	Provides the structured narrative and any pricing/negotiating frameworks that are used in the execution of the campaign	O	IO				O	O	O
				Prospect Campaign Consumables	##	Design specification of any consumables that are to be used in the execution of the campaign (e.g. brochures)	O	IO				O	O	O
					Prospect Campaign Consumable Type	The type of consumable item associated with the campaign (e.g. gift, brochure)	O	IO				O	O	O
					Prospect Campaign Consumable Description	The specification of the consumable item in whatever form appropriate. Note sourcing/procurement of the item is handled by execution)	O	IO				O	O	O
			Prospect Campaign Performance Record 	##		Maintains a record of the use and impact of prospect campaign versions over the life of the campaign	IO	IO			IO	IO	IO	O
				Prospect Campaign Procedure Instance Reference	##	Reference to the prospect campaign execution event	IO	IO			IO	IO	IO	O
					Employee/Business Unit Reference 	Reference to the business unit responsible for the campaign execution	IO	IO			IO	IO	IO	O
					Prospect Campaign Procedure Set-up	Details of the deployment set-up/configuration of the campaign for reference	IO	IO			IO	IO	IO	O
					Prospect Campaign Procedure Version Number	The prospect campaign version number used in the event	IO	IO			IO	IO	IO	O
					Prospect Campaign Procedure Result	The result/impact of the overall prospect campaign event (that can include multiple identified leads/opportunities)	I	IO			I	I	I	O
